CSERVE(8)

NAME
    cserve - SmallOS HTTP server

SYNOPSIS
    cserve [--host addr] [--port port] [--root path]
    cserve [--log off|error|info|debug] [--log-file path]
    cserve [--max-conn count] [--config path]

DESCRIPTION
    cserve starts the bundled HTTP server. It serves static files and uses the
    sample configuration installed with SmallOS unless command-line options
    override the defaults.

OPTIONS
    --host addr
        Bind address. The default is 0.0.0.0.

    --port port
        TCP port. The default is 8080.

    --root path
        Document root. The SmallOS image installs sample content in /var/www.

    --log off|error|info|debug
        Set log verbosity.

    --log-file path
        Write logs to path.

    --max-conn count
        Set the maximum connection count.

    --config path
        Load server options from an INI-style config file.

FILES
    /etc/cserve.ini
        Sample/default server configuration.

    /var/www
        Default web content in the SmallOS image.

SEE ALSO
    ftpd(8)
